## Layer 4: The Feedback Loop

Like TikTok's algorithm, docent keeps learning during the visit. This is passive — the visitor doesn't know it's happening.

### What Gets Tracked

Since this is voice-first, some signals are different from text chat:

| Signal | What It Means | Profile Update |
|---|---|---|
| Visitor asks a follow-up | They're interested | Increase `curiosity_level`, add to `topics_engaged` |
| Short response (1-5 words) | Low engagement | Flag `engagement_trend` declining |
| Visitor uses technical terms | Higher knowledge than assessed | Bump relevant `knowledge` field |
| "What?" / "Huh?" / "Wait, what?" | Went over their head | Lower `jargon_tolerance`, simplify |
| Laughter detected (or "haha" in transcript) | Humor is landing | Increase `humor_tolerance` |
| "Skip" / "Next" / "Move on" | Losing interest | Add to `topics_disengaged`, increase `pace` |
| Long, detailed spoken response | High engagement | Increase `depth_preference` |
| Silence > 10 seconds after docent finishes | May have walked away or zoned out | docent can prompt gently |
| Visitor interrupts docent mid-sentence | Response was too long | Shorten `preferred_response_length` |

### Implementation

After every visitor message, run a lightweight analysis:

```javascript
async function updateProfileFromInteraction(visitorTranscript, docentResponse, profile) {
  // Simple heuristics first (no API call needed)
  const wordCount = visitorTranscript.split(' ').length;

  if (wordCount <= 5) {
    profile.session.engagement_trend = adjustTrend(profile.session.engagement_trend, "down");
  } else if (wordCount >= 15) {
    // In spoken conversation, 15+ words is a substantial response
    profile.session.engagement_trend = adjustTrend(profile.session.engagement_trend, "up");
  }

  // Check for follow-up indicators
  const followUpPatterns = /\b(why|how|tell me more|what about|really|interesting|wait so|and then what)\b/i;
  if (followUpPatterns.test(visitorTranscript)) {
    profile.engagement.curiosity_level = Math.min(1, profile.engagement.curiosity_level + 0.05);
  }

  // Check for confusion indicators
  const confusionPatterns = /\b(what\??|huh|confused|don't get|lost me|english please|say that again|come again)\b/i;
  if (confusionPatterns.test(visitorTranscript)) {
    profile.communication.jargon_tolerance = Math.max(0, profile.communication.jargon_tolerance - 0.1);
  }

  // Check for humor response (spoken laughter often transcribes weirdly)
  const humorPatterns = /\b(ha ha|haha|hahaha|that's funny|hilarious|oh my god|no way|you're kidding)\b/i;
  if (humorPatterns.test(visitorTranscript)) {
    profile.communication.humor_tolerance = Math.min(1, profile.communication.humor_tolerance + 0.05);
  }

  // Check for boredom / skip signals
  const skipPatterns = /\b(next|skip|move on|what else|let's go|okay next|boring)\b/i;
  if (skipPatterns.test(visitorTranscript)) {
    profile.engagement.pace = "quick";
    // Whatever topic docent was on, it didn't land
    const currentTopic = extractCurrentTopic(docentResponse);
    if (currentTopic) profile.session.topics_disengaged.push(currentTopic);
  }

  // For deeper analysis, periodic lightweight API call (every 5th interaction)
  if (profile.session.pieces_viewed.length % 5 === 0) {
    await deepProfileUpdate(profile, visitorTranscript);
  }

  profile.last_updated = new Date().toISOString();
  await saveProfile(profile);
}
```

