## Voice Pipeline Architecture

Since docent is voice-first, the full pipeline for every interaction looks like this:

```
┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐
│ Visitor      │     │ STT          │     │ Acquaintance    │     │ TTS         │
│ speaks into  │────▶│ (Whisper)    │────▶│ Engine          │────▶│ (Coqui /    │
│ microphone   │     │              │     │                 │     │  OpenAI)    │
│              │     │ Returns:     │     │ 1. Update       │     │             │
└─────────────┘     │ transcript   │     │    profile      │     │ Returns:    │
                    └──────────────┘     │ 2. Build prompt │     │ audio       │
                                         │ 3. Get response │     │ stream      │
                                         │ 4. Return text  │     └──────┬──────┘
                                         └─────────────────┘            │
                                                                        ▼
                                                                 Visitor hears
                                                                 docent respond
```

### Latency Budget (Target: < 2 seconds end-to-end)

| Stage | Target | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| STT (Whisper) | 300-500ms | Use Whisper API streaming or on-device small model |
| Profile update | < 50ms | Local heuristics only, no API call |
| Prompt construction | < 10ms | Pure string building |
| LLM response | 500-800ms | OpenAI GPT-4o with streaming |
| TTS | 200-400ms | Stream first audio chunk before full response is done |
| **Total** | **~1.5s** | Feels like natural conversational pause |

### Streaming Strategy

Don't wait for the full LLM response before starting TTS. Stream it:

1. LLM starts returning tokens
2. After the first complete sentence, send it to TTS
3. TTS starts generating audio and streams it to the speaker
4. Meanwhile, LLM continues generating, next sentence queues up

This way the visitor hears docent start responding almost immediately.

